The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 07 October is 465,704 (827.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 October, there were 63,819 new confirmed cases (113.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 September, there were 38,469 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 66% (25350 extra cases).
